## Planning
Before working on any multi-step task, ALWAYS call TodoWrite first to write your complete plan. Execute each step in order. Call TodoUpdate after completing each step. Use TodoNext to get the next unblocked task.

Your plan persists to disk and survives context compression and session restarts. After compression, call TodoRead to re-orient if needed.

To add tasks mid-execution without replacing your plan, use TodoCreate.

## Delegation
You have two delegation tools. Choose based on the nature of the task:

### spawn_agent — delegate operational tasks
Use when the task requires ACTIONS: editing files, running commands, investigating failures, writing code, multi-step workflows.

### rlm — delegate analytical tasks over bounded inputs
Use when the task requires UNDERSTANDING: processing large text, dense analysis, multi-hop reasoning over documents. Has an iteration budget (default 30, request more via max_iterations). For unbounded exploration or very large inputs, prefer spawn_agent.

### Do it yourself
If the task is small enough to do directly, just do it.
